{"article_id":"swjpg4UymPq7hyy7","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Prominent North Korean websites were back online Tuesday","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"after an hours-long shutdown","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that led to speculation by some researchers and web watchers","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"that the country 's Internet connections could be under cyberattack .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"South Korean officials told the Associated Press","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"that Internet access to the North 's official Korean Central News Agency and the Rodong Sinmun newspaper were working normally Tuesday","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"after being inaccessible earlier .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Those sites are the main channels for official North Korea news , with servers","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"located abroad .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"The outage came","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"less than a week after the U.S. vowed an unspecified response to a massive hacking attack against Sony Pictures Entertainment over the release of the comedy film `` The Interview . ''","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"The plot of the comedy centers on the assassination of North Korean leader Kim Jong Un ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"leading to widespread speculation","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"that the country was responsible for the attack .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"Late last week , the FBI publicly blamed North Korea in the incident ,","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"though Pyongyang has denied involvement .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"The White House and the State Department on Monday declined to say","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"whether the U.S. government had any role in North Korea 's Internet problems .","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"`` We have no new information","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"to share","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"regarding North Korea today , ''","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"White House National Security Council spokesperson Bernadette Meehan told Fox News .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"`` If in fact North Korea ' s Internet has gone down ,","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"we ' d refer you to that government for comment . ''","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"North Korean diplomat Kim Song ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"asked Monday about the Internet attack ,","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"told The Associated Press :","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"`` I have no information . ''","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"North Korea is one of the least connected countries in the world .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"Few North Koreans have access to computers ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"and even those","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"who do","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"are typically able to connect only to a domestic intranet","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"that works with its own browsers , search engine and email programs ,","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"according to South Korea 's Unification Ministry .","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"Though North Korea is equipped for broadband Internet ,","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"only a small , approved segment of the population has any access to the World Wide Web .","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"More than a million people , however , are now using mobile phones in North Korea .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"The network covers most major cities","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"but users can not call outside the country or receive calls from outside .","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"Doug Madory , the director of Internet analysis at New Hampshire-based Dyn Research , a company","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"that studies Internet connectivity ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"the problems were discovered over the weekend","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"and grew progressively worse to the point","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"that `` North Korea 's totally down . ''","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"`` They have left the global Internet","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"and they are gone","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"until they come back , ''","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"one benign explanation for the problem was that a router may have suffered a software glitch ,","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"though a cyberattack","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"involving North Korea 's Internet service","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"was also a possibility .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"Routing instabilities are not uncommon ,","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"but this particular outage had gone on for hours","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"and was getting worse instead of better ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Madory said .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"`` This does n't fit that profile , '' of an ordinary routing problem ,","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"`` This shows something","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"getting progressively worse over time . ''","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"Another Internet technology service , Arbor Networks ,","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"which protects companies against hacker attacks ,","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"said","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"its monitoring detected denial-of-service attacks","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"aimed at North Korea 's infrastructure","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"starting Saturday","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"and persisting Monday .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"Such attacks transmit so much spurious data traffic to Internet equipment","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"that it becomes overwhelmed ,","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"until the attacks stop","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"or the spurious traffic can be filtered","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"and discarded","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"to allow normal connections to resume .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"President Obama said Friday","depth":3},{"id":77,"text":"that the U.S. government expected to respond `` proportionately '' to the hacking of Sony ,","depth":4},{"id":78,"text":"which he described as an expensive act of `` cyber vandalism ''","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"that he blamed on North Korea .","depth":5},{"id":80,"text":"Obama did not say","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"how the U.S. might respond .","depth":4},{"id":82,"text":"`` We are n't going to discuss ,","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"you know ,","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"publicly operational details about the possible response options or comment on those kind of reports in anyway","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"except to say","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"as we implement our responses ,","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"some will be seen ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"some may not be seen , ''","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"State Department spokeswoman Marie Harf said last week .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":181,"left":166,"right":180,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":118,"right":165,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":106,"right":117,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":99,"right":105,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":94,"right":98,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":0,"right":93,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":1,"right":92,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":96,"right":97,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":4,"right":95,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":95,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":103,"right":104,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":9,"right":102,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":10,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":11,"right":100,"relation":"cau